---
import MarketingChrome from "../layouts/MarketingChrome.astro";

const title = "Terms of Service · Bolt TMS";
const lastUpdated = "May 2026";
---

<MarketingChrome title={title} description="Terms governing use of Bolt marketing properties and Bolt TMS.">
    <article class="max-w-3xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-white/70">
        <h1 class="scroll-mt-24 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">
            Terms of service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-white/50">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p class="mt-5">
            These terms are a non-binding draft for the marketing site. Execute a formal
            Order Form or Master Subscription Agreement for production use of Bolt TMS.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Using our sites and services</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            By accessing bolttms.com properties, Bolt marketing pages, or Bolt TMS, you
            agree to follow applicable law, refrain from abusive use, and keep your
            account credentials confidential. We may suspend access for violations or risk
            to the platform.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Field tests and subscriptions</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            Field-test offerings (including duration, limits, and eligibility) are described at
            signup. After any field-test period, paid use is billed month-to-month according
            to the pricing and packaging in effect when you order, plus applicable taxes,
            unless your agreement says otherwise. Failure to pay may result in suspension
            or termination.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            Bolt retains all rights to the software, documentation, and branding. You
            retain rights to your business data. Limited feedback you provide may be used
            to improve the product without obligation to you.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Warranty disclaimer</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            Except where prohibited by law, Bolt provides the service “as is” and
            disclaims implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular
            purpose, and non-infringement. Bolt does not guarantee uninterrupted or
            error-free operation.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, neither party is liable for indirect,
            incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages. Bolt’s aggregate
            liability arising out of these terms generally should be capped as set forth
            in your formal agreement—replace this draft with executed contract terms.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            We may update these terms for the marketing site. Material changes to a
            production contract require the process defined in that contract.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            <a href="mailto:sales@boltsystem.com">sales@boltsystem.com</a>
            ·
            <a href="mailto:support@boltsystem.com">support@boltsystem.com</a>
        </p>
    </article>
</MarketingChrome>
